		<div>Ok, As a shammy I click cast from the spell gems.  No good mod has come out that has enlarged the actual icon..just the stupid placeholder.  Well I had enough of that and began to tweak some code around.  I suck at it but I discovered how to make the Icons bigger.<br />
<br />
1. I doubled the gemicons.tga files to be 512 x 512<br />
<br />
2. I edited in the eqanimations.xml file to make the icons be about 49 x 48 (couldnt quite get it)<br />
<br />
3. Edited my own little Spell Gem Bar to test it with..It only shows the BIG OLE icons and the place holder (when no spell equipped)<br />
<br />
I need someone with more xml experience to help with this I unlocked the door..now someone else needs to step in there and squish the mean ole spiders.  If i manage to make it all purty I'll repost.<br />
<br />
I couldnt get this dang forum to act right so I posted this on my old webpage.  Go to the link and click on the screenshot to download the zip file.  Just download the zip and replace all files you got with these. <br />
Test it out play with it and post your results.<br />
<br />
Download the 3 from here....<br />
<a href="http://www.geocities.com/lordjobu/" target="_blank">http://www.geocities.com/lordjobu/</a><br />
<br />
If you guys like em I'll actually post in the download section :P<br />
(So post what you think or MOD my mods and post your screenies)<br />
<br />
<br />
Tking mod posted under spell gems....ALL my mods work with the new patch now btw.<br />
<br />
<br />
Go to my old page there and download any of the 3 mods for this spell bar.  There is no longer a background or a border on any of the downloadables though only the Tking Screenshot shows this...you can drag the spellbar around by clicking just under the last icon and moving around.  Enjoy...Tking is the best one imo.<br />
<br />
This is the Tking Screenie for those who haven't seen<br />
<a href="http://www.eqgui.com/attachment.php?s=&amp;postid=14993" target="_blank">http://www.eqgui.com/attachment.php?s=&amp;postid=14993</a><br />
